📊 HR Analytics Dashboard
📌 Overview
This Power BI dashboard provides insights into employee attrition, job satisfaction, and workforce demographics. It helps HR teams identify trends, improve retention strategies, and enhance employee engagement.

🔹 Key Features
✔️ Employee Attrition Analysis – Overall attrition rate, employee count, and salary impact.
✔️ Demographic Insights – Attrition by age, gender, marital status, and education.
✔️ Job Role & Salary Trends – Job satisfaction levels and salary-wise attrition distribution.
✔️ Workforce Overview – Average employee age, salary, and industry trends.

🔹 Tools & Technologies
🔹 Power BI – Data visualization & interactive dashboards
🔹 SQL – Data querying & transformation
🔹 Excel – Data cleaning & preprocessing

📊 Dashboard Highlights
📉 Attrition Rate: 16.1% of employees left the company.
👨‍💼 Attrition by Age: Highest in the 26-35 age group (116 employees).
📍 Education Breakdown: Life Sciences & Medical backgrounds have the highest attrition.
💼 Job Satisfaction: Sales & Research roles report lower satisfaction.
💰 Salary Impact: Majority of employees leaving earn ≤5K, suggesting compensation concerns.

📂 Dataset Details
HR_Analytics.csv – Contains employee details, job roles, salaries, and attrition records.

🚀 How to Use
Download the .pbix file and open it in Power BI Desktop.
Explore different pages, filters, and interactive charts.
Customize reports using Power BI’s built-in tools.

